Go trough it without any power abilities, just regular Kirby. Eventually you will reach a high platform where an enemy that looks like a bomb with legs is walking. Eat it before it falls down and explodes. Kirby will have the Crash ability.
author: @CSLucasEpic

text:
I hope this means she'll play more Kirby games in the future. There's a commonly held belief among Kirby fans that while some are better than others, there are no actually bad Kirby games and I hope Gura will go on to discover that herself!

Kirby has something for everyone. 
Young children and people who just want to take it easy can typically beat the main stories with little difficulty. 
People who want a challenge can try to tackle the true arena. 
People who are into storytelling and deep lore can find an incredibly complex and interesting backstory, great worldbuilding, and plenty of mysteries to theorise about. 
On top of all that, you have great music, great level and boss design, and one of the cutest characters in videogames!
